The paper deals with the problem of estimating causal effects in a Bayesian network using observational data, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithms presented in the paper involve sampling and estimation, which are also common techniques in machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing the sample complexity and time complexity of the algorithms, which falls under the domain of theoretical computer science (cs.DS and cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with causal networks and interventions, which are relevant to control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY).
